ARLINGTON, Va. -- Police are investigating the possibility that the
person responsible for two recent gropings is the same man who
committed four plastic bag attacks earlier this year, WTOP has
learned.

In the most recent attacks -- which occurred in the past two nights --
the women were walking from the Rosslyn Metro station when a man
approached them, and groped them from behind.

Arlington County Police Detective Robert Icolari says the suspect
bears a physical resemblance to the man police identified as a suspect
in the plastic bag attacks, which ended in June.

In those attacks, the suspect tried to put a plastic bag over the
women's head before groping them.

No plastic bags were used or found in the two most recent attacks.
